'''Institute of Philology of the Siberian Branch of the RAS''' ({{lang-ru|Институт филологии СО РАН}}) is a research institute based in [[Akademgorodok]] of [[Novosibirsk]], [[Russia]].
==History== In 1966, the Institute of History, Philology, and Philosophy was created in Novosibirsk.<ref>[https://scfh.ru/en/papers/new-siberian-archaeology/ Science First Hand. New Siberian Archaeology.]</ref>
Institute of Philology was founded in 1990 as part of the United Institute of History, Philology and Philosophy of the Siberian Branch of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences|Academy of Sciences of the USSR]].<ref>[http://www.soran1957.ru/?p=auto&id=o0020074&ch=vitem Объединенный институт истории, филологии и философии. СО РАН.]</ref>
In 2006, the institute became an independent organization of the SB RAS<ref>[http://www.ras.ru/presidium/documents/directions.aspx?ID=03367a27-95c9-4c9a-8b59-bed692a11af3 О реорганизации и переименовании институтов Сибирского отделения РАН (представление Отделения). Официальный сайт РАН.]</ref>
